== 5. Nf3 · Paulsen Attack ==
This is the main line for White, sometimes called the Paulsen Attack.<ref>[http://chesstempo.com/gamedb/opening/592]</ref><ref>[http://www.365chess.com/opening.php?m=10&n=711&ms=e4.e6.d4.d5.e5.c5.c3.Nc6.Nf3]</ref> Of Black's several responses, the main line is [[/5...Qb6|5...Qb6]], adding pressure to White's d4 pawn and continuing development.

[[/5...Bd7|5...Bd7]], the Euwe Variation, is a good alternative move that has some strong proponents.<ref><http://www.chess.com/video/player/why-simon-loves-the-french-the-advance-variation></ref>

